Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{some}, season with
@salt{some} and @pepper{some}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of
#baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a
bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick. Season with
@salt{some} and @pepper{some}.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. In another medium bowl,
combine the @panko breadcrumbs{50%grams}, @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}
and the @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely
coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{some} to coat the
bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3
> mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, and fry until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a #large baking tray{}, then bake on the middle shelf
until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken bakes, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%grams}. Trim the
@baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Carefully discard the hot oil from the chicken pan, then wipe out and return to
medium-high heat.

Pour in the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to
the boil, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @sriracha sauce{30%grams} and @honey{15%grams} until thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once your buffalo sauce has thickened, stir through the @crème fraîche{75%grams}
until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{some} and @pepper{some}.

Add a splash of @water{some} if it's a little too thick, then remove from the
heat.

When the chips have 5 mins left, in a medium bowl, combine the baby gem with
the @honey and mustard dressing{30%grams}. Season with @salt{some} and
@pepper{some}.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per person) into the oven to warm through,
~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, thinly slice the crispy chicken.

Share the tortillas between your plates. Top with the salad, crispy chicken
slices, a drizzle of buffalo sauce and a sprinkle of cheese - as much as you'd
like.

Serve your tacos and chips with the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!